### 3.2 Service B â€“ Logger & Reporter

#### 3.2.1 Event Subscription & Logging

- Subscribe to Redis channels from Service A.
- Log received events into MongoDB with full metadata.
- Store relevant time-series data separately if needed for validation.

#### 3.2.2 Log Query API

- Provide REST endpoints to query logs based on:
  - Event type
  - Date/time range
  - Source or filename
- Support pagination and sorting.

#### 3.2.3 PDF Report Generation

- Generate PDF reports using RedisTimeSeries data.
- Use `TS.RANGE`/`TS.MRANGE` to fetch metrics.
- Visualize with charts (line/bar) and summaries.
- Return report as downloadable PDF.
